      "role": "user",
      "content": "That's a good start. I specifically want to look at the argument that any state involvement in content moderation—even if it's just defining what is \"harmful\"—is effectively state censorship. Can you expand on how a philosopher like John Stuart Mill might argue that this kind of regulation stifles the \"marketplace of ideas\" and why that's such a critical point for my post?",
